Hi Florian, I encountered the same error and also this message while running tests on a current Moodle 5.0 build Deprecation: cron_setup_user has been deprecated since 4.2. Use \core\cron::setup_user() instead. See MDL-77837 for more information. some searching led me to https://github.com/open-lms-open-source/moodle-mod_hsuforum/issues/42 where mod_hsuforum gets fixed. Applying the same method (replacing all occurences of "cron_setup_user" with "\core\cron::setup_user") in /scheduler/classes/task/send_reminders.php I modified the last few lines of send_reminders.php to this and can now run the task again without errors: 
```text
            // Send reminder to all students in the slot.


            foreach ($slotm->get_appointments() as $appointment) {


                $student = $DB->get_record('user', array('id' => $appointment->studentid));


                \core\cron::setup_user($student, $course);


                \scheduler_messenger::send_slot_notification($slotm,


                        'reminder', 'reminder', $teacher, $student, $teacher, $student, $course);


            }


        }


        \core\cron::setup_user();


    }


}
```

